<paragraph blockId="7.[264,1323,1719,1905]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Although 
<taxonomicName box="[384,574,1719,1744]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Bilyaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mariae">
<emphasis box="[384,574,1719,1744]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bilyaxia mariae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles by its body­shape and costate elytra the representatives of 
<taxonomicName box="[368,503,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Ctenoderus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[368,503,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Ctenoderus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[570,743,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Cylindrophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[570,743,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cylindrophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it should be transferred to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1225,1322,1759,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Bilyaxia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1225,1322,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Bilyaxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because of its ocellate sculpture of its pronotum and prosternal process, its unmodified anal sternite, and the form of its antennal sensory organs.
</paragraph>
